Even we have 18 millions galaxies, their cKDTree size is super small. But we need to collect positions of (px, py, pz) to a dataframe gpdf (446MB) as an input for generating the cKDTree. Any way to directly generate the cKDTree from the spark/dataframe galdf with bypassing the gpdf?

In [20]:
edge_schema = T.StructType([\
                            T.StructField('src', T.IntegerType(), False),\
                            T.StructField('dst', T.IntegerType(), False),\
                           ])
galedf = sqlContext.createDataFrame([],edge_schema)
